          "tz": 330
        },
        "subject": "LU-8496 llog: avoid llog cancel race",
        "message": "LU-8496 llog: avoid llog cancel race\n\nConcurrently running two or more lfs changelog_clear need to be\nprotected against races. llog_process_thread() used to read llogs\nwithout taking into account that the llog being read may be destroyed\nby another process. This patch serializes changelog cancellings using\nllog_ctxt's mutex.\n\nAlso includes the test/reproducer for the same.\n\nSigned-off-by: Vladimir Saveliev <vladimir_saveliev@xyratex.com>\nSigned-off-by: Rahul Deshmukh <rahul.deshmukh@seagate.com>\nSeagate-bug-id: MRP-1443\nChange-Id: I207815ec17640795e68fe2fd0151e2667b7d9be1\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
